    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"> <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19662127/Baking\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19662127\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Baking</a> allows users to pre-compute or &quot;bake&quot; pattern networks into 2D texture images or 3D point clouds. </span></p><h3 id=\"BakinginMaya-BakePatterns\">Bake Patterns</h3><p>Add <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661581/PxrBakeTexture\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661581\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PxrBakeTexture</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19662125/PxrBakePointCloud\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19662125\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PxrBakePointCloud</a> patterns into your shading network in places where you want to bake that state of the network into a texture or point cloud.  When doing regular renders, baked textures will be used by these patterns, and when doing bake renders, textures will be baked. ie. written to disk.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" width=\"300\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544543018/rfmBakeNetwork.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591252&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=300&amp;height=327\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544543018/rfmBakeNetwork.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591252&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544543038\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfmBakeNetwork.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544543018\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"a768b2ba-f058-4f08-93a5-6ce9c9699d8a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544543018/rfmBakeNetwork.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591252&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=340&amp;height=371 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544543018/rfmBakeNetwork.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591252&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=300&amp;height=327 1x\"></span> </p><h3 id=\"BakinginMaya-StartingaBakeRender\">Starting a Bake Render</h3><p>A bake render is essentially a batch render with one different setting. It uses the bake Hider instead of the raytrace Hider.   To start a bake render simply choose Bake Render instead of Batch Render from the RenderMan menu.   All the usual <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539308/RenderMan+Preferences#RenderManPreferences-BatchPreferences\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539308\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">batch render preferences</a> apply to the bake render.  The baked textures will be written to the locations specified in the individual PxrBakeTexture or PxrBakePointCloud patterns.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" confluence-query-params=\"effects=drop-shadow\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544543018/rfmBakeMenuItem.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591253&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;effects=drop-shadow\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544543018/rfmBakeMenuItem.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431591253&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544543041\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfmBakeMenuItem.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544543018\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"1d4da6a0-1cb2-42b0-8757-f8585d2bfd80\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p>"
    }
